Let us discuss  the value of resummed coefficient and its  dependence  on the scale of factorization $\mu_F$. Below we present results for two cases.
a) $\mu_F$ is equal to kinematic hard scale $\mu_F=M_V$ ($L=0$), and b)  $\mu_F$ is chosen to vanish the value of the first high energy term $C_1$, it requires $\mu_F=M_V/2=m$ ($L=\ln 4$):
